This paper focuses on the development of a computer aided diagnosis system for lung cancer detection using deep learning techniques. The paper specifically addresses the problems of false positive reduction and nodule segmentation, which are both important tasks in lung cancer diagnosis. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of semi-supervised learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.MS) and neural networks (cs.NE).
